.Dd March 8, 2026
.Dt AGEV 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm agev_get_age_bracket ,
.Nm agev_set_age ,
.Nm agev_set_dob
.Nd get and set user age information
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libutil
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In libutil.h
.Ft int *
.Fn agev_get_age_bracket "const char *username"
.Ft int
.Fn agev_set_age "const char *username" "int age"
.Ft int
.Fn agev_set_dob "const char *username" "const char *dob"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn agev_get_age_bracket
function returns the age bracket for a user as an array of two integers.
The
.Fn agev_set_age
function sets the age for a user. This function may only be called by the root user.
The
.Fn agev_set_dob
function sets the date of birth for a user. This function may only be called by the root user.
The date of birth is a string in the format YYYY-MM-DD.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn agev_get_age_bracket
function returns a pointer to an array of two integers, or NULL on error.
The caller is responsible for freeing the memory allocated for the array.
The
.Fn agev_set_age
and
.Fn agev_set_dob
functions return 0 on success and -1 on error.
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Fn agev_set_age
and
.Fn agev_set_dob
functions will fail if:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EPERM
The caller is not the root user.
.It Bq Er EINVAL
The specified user does not exist.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr agectl 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn get_age_bracket ,
.Fn set_age ,
and
.Fn set_dob
functions first appeared in MidnightBSD 4.0.
